@node Main "Totematik - Documentation"

                            'Totematik' 1.03

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Totematik' is a @{" Workbench game " link play} played on an 8 by 8 tiles
board in which you have to recreate 10 totems in various
orientations, upright, upside down, lying on their side either
to the left or to the right.

  Each totem has a 'T' shape and has 5 parts: left and right
wings, a head, which is located between wings, a center body
portion and a footing. To create a totem, the parts must be at
the appropriate places. In addition to the totem pieces, 13
'filler' blocks that can also be moved; these blocks can either
hinder or help you in recreating the totems.

  Have fun!

               @{" Install and Play the game " link play}
               @{"   Features of the game    " link features}
               @{"          History          " link histo}
