@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Totematik" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on any tile located next to the empty space
(indicated by an 'inverted' tile), if the move is possible, the clicked
tile will go there.

  Each totem has a 'T' shape and includes 5 parts: a left wing, a right
wing (both have a triangular shape), a head which is located between
the wings (it has a cross shape), a center body portion located under
the head and a footing, which is the lowest part.

  To create a totem, the parts must be at their appropriate places: the
wings must be placed so their straight portions are located on either
side and in line with the upper portion of the head part of a totem.
The center body portion has an 'angle' displayed on the middle and that
angle must be pointed toward the head of the totem. As for the foot
part, obviously it will have to be located at the base of the totem. To
make matters simpler, depending on the orientation of a totem, all
associated parts have the same colour, so you can see which parts goes
with which totem.

  In addition to the totem parts, 13 'filler' blocks can be moved as
you wish, these blocks and their position have no importance whatsoever,
they are just there to help or complicate the game...

  A display, on the lower right in the window, shows the number of
totems that are currently recreated, when that number gets to 10, the
game is complete!

  Try to recreate all totems in the minimum amount of moves possible. 

  Note that you can restart a game anytime by clicking on the 'New Game'
button (or with the Right-Amiga and 'N' keys).

  Have fun!

@endnode

